Vladimir Mikhailovich Filippov (Russian: Влади́мир Миха́йлович Фили́ппов; born 15 April 1951) is the President of the Peoples' Friendship University of Russia, Minister of Education of the Russian Federation in 1998–2004, Doctor in physical and mathematical sciences, professor and academician of the Russian Academy of Education.

He was born on 15 April 1951 in the town of Uryupinsk, Stalingrad Region (now the Volgograd Region). In 1968 he entered Patrice Lumumba University of Peoples' Friendship. In 1973, Filippov graduated the Faculty Science (major: mathematics)... In June 1993, Filippov was elected as the Rector of Peoples' Friendship University of Russia until 1998, when he was appointed as the Minister of education of the Russian Federation and held this post during the work of four RF Cabinets of ministers.

His wife, a graduate of the Volgograd Polytechnic Institute, works as a school teacher. Son and daughter graduated from the Economics Department of RUDN. Daughter Irina Filippova works as a TV presenter (creative pseudonym – Irena Ponaroshku).

Filippov is an author of more than 200 scientific and methodological publications including 30 monographs...

Summary: 
Vladimir Filippov, born April 15, 1951, in Uryupinsk, is a Russian politician and academic who served as the Minister of Education of the Russian Federation from 1998 to 2004. He holds a doctorate in physical and mathematical sciences and is currently the President of the Peoples' Friendship University of Russia (RUDN). In his personal life, his wife is a teacher, and he has a son and a daughter, the latter being TV presenter Irina Filippova (Irena Ponaroshku). He is also a prolific scholar with over 200 scientific publications.
